From:sea_biscuit

As a follow-up to my previous post...

It is far easier for companies to be Dividend Achievers than to be "Earnings
Achievers" (to coin a new term). Therefore, it is more likely that our
portfolio of Earnings Achievers has a higher turnover than the one that has the
Dividend Achievers...

Ironically, the former would be in a taxable account while it is the latter
that would be in a tax-sheltered account! Well, looks like we cannot have it
all, I guess! :-((

Dipy.
