%BOM---------------------
Date:6/16/1997 12:21:00 PM
From:P. Ramamoorthy

AIMM, SEPR, and neurogen were all discussed in Barron's in 1994 or earlier by
an analyst. The business model of these companies is quite different from
traditional biotechs, namely,
(1) they have a major buisness partner funding product development and
marketing, (focusing on specific drugs and markets)
(2) the drugs they were developing were part of certain existing FDA approved
drugs (e.g. SEPR separating out effective isomers from poor quality mixtures of
certain existing drugs on the market), or natural resource (AIMM extracting
compounds from natural sources implying fewer side effects and faster FDA
approval) etc.
If the stuck to business models like these, their cash burn rate is not the
same other biotechs. Ram
